5 \u03bcL of 97% EDC in 470.5 \u03bcL of distilled water. EDC solutions must be stored at -20 \u00baC.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">It's convenient to prepare freshly EDC solutions for assuring proper conjugation, unless it will be used within the following days consecutively.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830272,"guid":"A23E08A0F39211E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830271,"previous_guid":"EFA1B2F0F39111E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"8176CA76CB0E406886FE30B1461FD42C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Reactive Preparations"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"D2A10B6959674FA58C39A25688AF2DE8","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Reconstitute the aptamers by pipetting 30 \u03bcL of 100 \u03bcM stock on an empty eppendorf tube. Place in a thermoblock at 95 \u00baC for 10 minutes. And move the tube quickly to an ice bath, letting them to cool down for 10 minutes more. The reconstituted aptamer can be kept at 4\u00baC for several weeks, or store freezed at -20 \u00baC for long periods.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830273,"guid":"8DA873C0F39311E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830272,"previous_guid":"A23E08A0F39211E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"0AE582B774BA48FEA37C50B78927F030","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Latex beads preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"47BECC2EF2C74260AB5B8D80C38D9BD9","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Dilute  200 \u00b5L of 2.5 % wt beads stock with 300\u00b5L of additional MES buffer. Reaching a final volume of 500 \u00b5L. <\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830274,"guid":"D99C1DE0F39311E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830273,"previous_guid":"8DA873C0F39311E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"440C06C476FE421194EF90054380014C","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Latex beads preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9CD84AD5E99D45A692CB73A0267A7FA0","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"> the tube at 15.000 rpm for 4minutes. Discard the supernatant and resuspend them in 500 \u00b5L of MES buffer. <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">\nFor beads resuspension, repeated pipetting it's highly recommended, aspiring and blowing out in the eppendorf tube. It's crucial assuring perfect beads disperssion, if little agreggates are appreciated, try reducing centrifugation times or sonicating the beads for resuspension (5 minutes sonication at moderate power).<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"BE493C80F39811E988B909D4AF391C07","order_id":2,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"15000","guid":"BE493C80F39811E988B909D4AF391C07","id":0,"label":"4 minutes","unit":33}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830275,"guid":"03C062C0F39411E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830274,"previous_guid":"D99C1DE0F39311E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F0C415E2378848B9A5A056E561EE469B","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Latex beads Conjugation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"FBEA75B9597F4A45982CCB86DE879B95","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Mix on an eppendorf tube 40 \u00b5L of sulfo-NHS 0.4 M , 40 \u00b5L of 5' amino terminal modified aptamer and 40 \u00b5L of 0.32 M EDC solution.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830285,"guid":"CB663D70F39611E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830275,"previous_guid":"03C062C0F39411E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"E09FA673B22A4F9895024B3671E93AB9","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Latex beads Conjugation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"8F5A21E60A3D4EACB55611AA6762D6BB","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Vortex for 20 seconds the prepared 500 \u00b5L latex bead suspension in MES and add quickly 160 \u00b5L of the conjugation solution prepared in step 6.<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830286,"guid":"FE334E50F39611E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830285,"previous_guid":"CB663D70F39611E988B909D4AF391C07","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"CE1A38E791AD4B1DB9FFAD8F37B70D8F","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Latex beads Conjugation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B607D4A8F0FD460B8198DFC36BC7F909","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Cover with aluminium foil or tape the eppendorf tube, and Incubate  the prepared solution for 1h 30 minutes at room temperature with strong agitation. (250 rpm on a thermoblock agitator is recommended).<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#84CE84","critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":830297,"guid":"93F46730F39711E988B909D4AF391C07","previous_id":830300,"previous_guid":"5EE16880F39811E988B90